# shadcn/ui Usage - STRICT ENFORCEMENT

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for **ALL** UI elements. **NO CUSTOM UI COMPONENTS ARE PERMITTED.**

## CRITICAL RULES

### ✅ REQUIRED
- **ONLY** use shadcn/ui components for all UI elements
- **ALL** buttons, inputs, cards, dialogs, forms, and other UI elements **MUST** come from shadcn/ui
- Components are located in `src/components/ui/` after installation
- Import components from `@/components/ui/[component-name]`
- This project is in dark mode so make sure there are no dark colored text on
  dark backgrounds (and vice versa)

### ❌ FORBIDDEN
- **NEVER** create custom UI components (buttons, inputs, cards, etc.)
- **NEVER** write custom styling for basic UI elements that shadcn/ui provides
- **NEVER** use unstyled HTML elements like `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>` directly
- **NEVER** create wrapper components that bypass shadcn/ui components

## Initialization

If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, use the following command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

To add a specific component (for example, the button component), use:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

**ALWAYS** install the shadcn/ui component before using it. If a component doesn't exist in `src/components/ui/`, install it first.

## Required shadcn/ui Components

When building UI features, you **MUST** use these shadcn/ui components:
- `button` - For **ALL** button interactions (including Clerk auth buttons)
- `card` - For **ALL** content containers
- `input` - For **ALL** form inputs
- `dialog` - For **ALL** modals and dialogs (including Clerk auth flows)
- `form` - For **ALL** form handling with validation
- `toast` - For **ALL** notifications
- `dropdown-menu` - For **ALL** dropdown menus
- `table` - For **ALL** data tables
- `tabs` - For **ALL** tabbed interfaces
- `select` - For **ALL** select dropdowns
- `textarea` - For **ALL** multi-line text inputs
- `checkbox` - For **ALL** checkboxes
- `label` - For **ALL** form labels

Install any component as needed with `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`.

## Clerk Integration - REQUIRED APPROACH

### Authentication Buttons

**ALL** Clerk sign in and sign up buttons **MUST** use shadcn/ui Button components:

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";

// ✅ CORRECT - Use shadcn/ui Button
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline">Sign Up</Button>
</SignUpButton>
```

### Authentication Flows

**ALWAYS** use `mode="modal"` for Clerk authentication to launch sign in/sign up in a modal dialog:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Modal mode
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

// ❌ WRONG - Redirect mode (don't use this)
<SignInButton mode="redirect">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>
```

### User Button

For the Clerk UserButton component, wrap it in shadcn/ui components when needed:

```typescript
import { UserButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";

// Use UserButton directly (it has its own styling)
<UserButton afterSignOutUrl="/" />
```

## Examples

### ✅ CORRECT - Using shadcn/ui components:

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Dialog, DialogTrigger, DialogContent } from "@/components/ui/dialog";

export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>My Card</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Input placeholder="Enter text..." />
        <Dialog>
          <DialogTrigger asChild>
            <Button>Open Dialog</Button>
          </DialogTrigger>
          <DialogContent>
            {/* Dialog content */}
          </DialogContent>
        </Dialog>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

### ❌ WRONG - Custom UI components:

```typescript
// NEVER DO THIS
export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="border rounded-lg p-4">
      <h2>My Card</h2>
      <input type="text" placeholder="Enter text..." />
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Enforcement

If a shadcn/ui component exists for a UI element you need, you **MUST** use it. There are no exceptions to this rule.
